>> source: https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/recipes/orzo-tomato-soup
>> time required: 30 minutes
>> image: https://images.immediate.co.uk/production/volatile/sites/30/2020/08/tomato-and-orzo-soup-47fe2e7.jpg?resize=768,574

Heat 1 tbsp @olive oil{2%tbsp} in a large saucepan. Add the @onion{1} and @celery{2} and fry for ~{10-15%min}s, or until starting to soften, then add the @garlic{2%clove} and cook for ~{1%min} more. Stir in all the @other{150%g} ingredients, except for the @pesto{2%tbsp} and remaining oil, and bring to the boil.

Reduce the heat and leave to simmer for ~{6-8%min}s, or until the pasta is tender. Season to taste, then ladle into bowls.

Stir the remaining oil with the pesto, then drizzle over the soup. Serve with chunks of @crusty bread{}.
